In a joint press conference, President Trump and King Abdullah of Jordan discussed several key issues, including the recent chemical attack in Syria. President Trump condemned the attack and expressed his responsibility to respond to it. He also criticized the previous administration's handling of the Syrian crisis. King Abdullah expressed his optimism that President Trump will succeed in brokering peace between Israel and Palestine and discussed the role of Arab countries in supporting this effort. The leaders also touched on the fight against terrorism, the refugee crisis, and the Iranian militias in Syria. President Trump vowed to take action against terrorism and criticized the Iran nuclear deal. The conference concluded with both leaders expressing their commitment to working together to bring peace and stability to the Middle East.